Title: Critical WordPress Exploit Chain
Findings: CVE-2018-7600 (Drupalgeddon2, chained with XSS CVE-2014-3704), Host: 192.168.1.100 (Mr. Robot VM). Multi-stage: Stored XSS steals session → RCE uploads malicious plugin. Impact: Full root access.
Remediation: Update Drupal/WordPress to latest (plugins too), enable WAF (ModSecurity rules for XSS), sanitize inputs (esc_html), disable file uploads for non-admins. Rescan verified fix. CVSS: 9.8.
